In fact, women and men express that reproduction is indeed about women’s autonomy. Arguably, it seems that what women truly desire and deserve is legality, accessibility, and professionalism, along with the freedom to decide whether they will or will not pursue an abortion. Without acquiring what women already declare they want, we risk continuing misogynistic, dehumanizing, and misogynoiric experiences for the foreseeable future.

be discussed with these stakeholders prior to publication.
Unless the legislation is amended to include more inclusive language, organizations—particularly service providers—not affected by the law fail to understand (i.e. they do not listen to) or understand outsiders’ experiences. As such, the recommendations in this report have been formulated in a broader more inclusive manner.
